SIMPLE: encephaloid
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Encephaloid
<hw>En*ceph"a*loid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'egke`falos</grk> + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <def>Resembling the
material of the brain; cerebriform.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Encephaloid cancer</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>, <cd>a
very malignant form of cancer of brainlike consistency. See under
<er>Cancer</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Encephaloid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Encephaloid
<hw>En*ceph"a*loid</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An encephaloid
cancer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Encephalology</ent>⟦br⟧
